title: Number of oncology practices in the U.S. by region and size 2013
summary: This grouped bar chart represents 4 different Countrys on X-axis for 3 groups 1-2 physicians, 3-6 physicians, and 7 or more physicians. On the Y-axis it shows their corresponding Number of new patients.
Out of all 3 groups, 7 or more physicians had the highest Number of new patients in Country South and 1-2 physicians had the lowest Number of new patients in Country West.
Among all the Countrys, 1-2 physicians had the highest Number of new patients in Country South and lowest Number of new patients in Country West.
Country South and West had the biggest gap of 35.0 between the highest and lowest Number of new patients found for 1-2 physicians.
min_summary: This grouped bar chart shows Number of new patients on the Y-axis for 4 different Countrys for 3 groups 1-2 physicians, 3-6 physicians, and 7 or more physicians that are presented on the X-axis.
Out of all 3 groups, 7 or more physicians had the highest Number of new patients in Country South and 1-2 physicians had the lowest Number of new patients in Country West.

max_summary: This grouped bar chart represents 4 different Countrys on X-axis for 3 groups 1-2 physicians, 3-6 physicians, and 7 or more physicians. On the Y-axis it shows their corresponding Number of new patients.
Country South had the maximum Number of new patients among all 3 groups, and it was for 7 or more physicians. The minimum Number of new patients was observed in Country West for 1-2 physicians.
In Country South, 1-2 physicians had the highest Number of new patients among all 4 Countrys and it has the lowest Number of new patients in Country West.
Country South and West had the biggest gap of 35.0 between the highest and lowest Number of new patients found for 1-2 physicians.
Among the groups, 1-2 physicians had the biggest difference in Number of new patients. Where the maximum Number of new patients was 2.46 times larger than the minimum Number of new patients.

7 or more physicians had the maximum Number of new patients out of all 3 groups in Country South followed by 7 or more physicians in South, and the minimum Number of new patients is found for 1-2 physicians in West.
Averaging all 3 groups 1-2 physicians, 3-6 physicians, and 7 or more physicians, the Country South is the maximum Number of new patients and Northeast is the minimum Number of new patients.
